---
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | Creative License">
  <section class="about-page">
    <header class="about-hero">
      <h1 class="about-kicker">Creative License</p>
      <h1 class="intro">is a thesis project about rules as creative force.</h1>
      <p class="about-intro">
        The site treats <strong>constraint</strong> as a method, not a <strong>limitation</strong>.
        Each section documents a different relationship to <strong>rules</strong>, from the
        <strong>external structures</strong> that shape production to the <strong>internal habits</strong>
        that guide decision-making.
      </p>
   
    </header>
   <div class="about-question-box">
         <h1 class="about-question"> Do rules actually limit creativity—or do they make
          it better?
        </h1>

      </div>
    <div class="about-grid">
      <article class="about-panel">
        <h2>How it started</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>CREATIVE LICENSE</strong> is an ongoing experiment built from <strong>rules</strong>
          collected from students at <strong>SUNY New Paltz</strong>. Things like “Have a plan,”
          “Don’t think, just do,” or “You can’t delete anything once it’s placed.” Instead of
          ignoring them, I <strong>followed them</strong>. Literally.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="about-panel">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>
          Through <strong>workshops</strong>, <strong>typographic studies</strong>, and
          <strong>physical + digital experiments</strong>, I tested what happens when you let
          <strong>rules</strong> take control of the process. Sometimes they worked. Sometimes they
          completely <strong>broke the outcome</strong>. But every time, they pushed the work
          somewhere <strong>unexpected</strong>.
        </p>
      </article>

      <div class="about-split">
        <article class="about-panel about-panel--split">
          <h2>The structure</h2>
          <div class="about-structure">
            <p class="about-structure-lead">
              The project is organized into three parts.
            </p>
            <ul class="about-structure-list">
              <li>
                <span class="about-structure-title"><strong>Rules of the Work</strong></span>
                <span class="about-structure-copy"><strong>what you’re making</strong></span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="about-structure-title"><strong>Rules of the Craft</strong></span>
                <span class="about-structure-copy"><strong>how you make it</strong></span>
              </li>
              <li>
                <span class="about-structure-title"><strong>Rules of the Self</strong></span>
                <span class="about-structure-copy"><strong>how you think while making it</strong></span>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="about-panel about-panel--split">
          <h2>What it means</h2>
          <p>
            This isn’t about <strong>restriction</strong>. It’s about using <strong>structure</strong>
            as a <strong>tool</strong>. Because the truth is—you’re already following
            <strong>rules</strong>. You just might not realize it yet.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    width: min(100%, var(--size-page-width));
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2.5rem) var(--size-page-padding) 4rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-hero,
  .about-panel {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-inner);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  .about-question-box {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
    border-radius: var(--radius-inner);
    background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
    padding: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .about-hero {
    padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-hero h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 7vw, 5.5rem);
    line-height: 0.92;
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    max-width: 15ch;
    font-weight: normal;
  }

    .about-kicker {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--color-background);
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    background: white;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 150, "wght" 900, "slnt" 0;
    rotate: -2deg;
    transition: all 0.35s ease;
  }
   .about-kicker:hover {
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 150, "wght" 500, "slnt" 0;
    rotate: -0deg;
    transition: all 0.35s ease;
  }
  .about-intro,
  .about-question,
  .about-panel p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .about-question {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 150, "wght" 700, "slnt" 0;
    line-height: 1.35;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    transition: font-variation-settings 0.35s ease;

  }
    .about-question:hover {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-variation-settings: "wdth" 170, "wght" 900, "slnt" 0;
    line-height: 1.35;
    width: fit-content;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
transition: font-variation-settings 0.35s ease;
  }


  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-split {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .about-panel {
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 2rem);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-structure {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .about-structure-lead {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 1.5vw, 1.15rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 38ch;
  }

  .about-structure-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-structure-list li {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.2rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-inner);
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
  }

  .about-structure-title {
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-structure-copy {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  .about-panel h2 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--font-headings);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }

  .about-panel--split {
    height: 100%;
  }

  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .about-split {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

</style>